article.description: Tre' Coggins scored a career-high 21 and Lionheart Leslie made a pair of layups in the final 26 seconds as Cal State-Fullerton closed on a 7-0 run to beat Pacific 77-76 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Coggins, Leslie lift Cal State-Fullerton over Pacific, 77-76
article.linkText: Coggins, Leslie lift Cal State-Fullerton over Pacific, 77-76
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- Tre' Coggins scored a career-high 21 and Lionheart Leslie made a pair of layups in the final 26 seconds as Cal State-Fullerton closed on a 7-0 run to beat Pacific 77-76 Tuesday night. A pair of free throws by Ray Bowles gave Pacific a 76-70 lead with 3:05 to play before Khalil Ahmad hit one free throw and Malcolm Brooks hit two to pull Cal State-Fullerton within three with 70 seconds left. Bowles missed a jumper for Pacific before a layup by Leslie made it 76-75. After a steal by Fullerton's Kennedy Esume, another layup by Leslie gave the Titans their first lead since the game's opening seconds. Fullerton (1-1) got a stop and Pacific was forced to foul, but Leslie missed both free throws. A half-court shot by Pacific's TJ Wallace fell short as time expired. Bowles had 22 points and 10 rebounds, both career highs, to lead Pacific (0-2).
